  "text": "The aluminium production process (typically Hall-Heroult process), can be subdivided into four major process areas namely: anode area, rodding area, potrooms, and ingot mill. In the anode area, the raw materials are taken into the plant and the anodes are manufactured. The rodding area has two main activities. The first is to attach a rod to the baked anode in order to suspend it in the pot. The second activity is to remove the remains of the baked anode. The potrooms contain reduction cells (pot), which contain anodes, cathodes, and bath (liquid electrolyte). The molten aluminium from the potrooms will be sent through to ingot mill, which further cast it into ingots [CITATION_1] . The simple flow sheet of the aluminium smelting process is shown in Fig. 3 .",
